           SPELL=gpsd
         VERSION=2.20
       BUILD_API=2
          SOURCE=$SPELL-${VERSION}.tar.gz
SOURCE_DIRECTORY=$BUILD_DIRECTORY/$SPELL-$VERSION
   SOURCE_URL[0]=http://download.berlios.de/gpsd/$SOURCE
          MD5[0]=a524f9a7481a62ad71ade65ce0c0483d 
        WEB_SITE=http://gpsd.berlios.de/
         ENTERED=20040217
         UPDATED=20050323
	LICENSE=GPL
          SHORT="GPSD is a gps translator."
cat << EOF
Gpsd is a translator. It takes input from a device capable of generating positional data (like a GPS or a Loran receiver) and translates it into another, very simple format. Gpsd re-publishes the data on a networking port via ip. Clients can connect to this port and request data at their leisure. 
EOF
